brugge Rophael Coots
M ons gisteren was aen ul mijnen lesten, waer aen mij referere deser allen
tot versoeck dat soo haest thomas porter arriveert ul het pack met spaens
lakens N 45 per waegens geheft herrewaerts te senden, mits conditie, dat het
selve soo halft, als de hulse packen konde hier wesen alsoo tselve niet eerde
noodigh hebbe, waer wel om die tijdt oft een dagh ten langhsten langer
wat passeert verneme geirne en naer groetenisse blijve
london henry maynard
19 ditto
B my last to you on the 12 courant with remise for £178:5:6 sterlu
in 2 sererall bills for yd aust, which I hope is com fafe to yd kends
sence rec yd of 4 p ditto: yd bill for mine autt of £109- shall
beduely descharged, I supose excull fall much more cusseed of pafing
because of the gallivens beeng arrived in spaine, I shall endeavour all
I can to compley imss you in all respecte, will knowing the arhiles
of our aggreement, in which shall no neon feule for as much lyes
in my poever: shall give you credit for the goods shipped aboard
cramp, p enpect the nortrens to conce by pindar, soo mish is
well arrived att ostend, inclosed & instructions for one bale of sine
cloathes more which pray & dispasch as soone possible, for shall
much want them haven haveing sold all the bale N 39 butt 3 piec
resting which will go of quickley endeavour to have good goods, & inlcour
I have reed the 6 & silver marn they are of the long ones & tisshim you
must solliecte the make the make to for mar lenght I goods nees
for these are tothin & the lengh tis not ast all considered of wee had
had is p more before now they should have seen sold, butt they
cominy solate will do no goods, for the faters must have most their
provession teady by sber. whower you pleaseto procure no lest then
10 p before castonas, & in case be well make the formar sort in
lenght & prife, aggree with hin tough for the 15: in case in bandiere
sende any packettes of lace to me, I'll take carcto dispatch them as
do for others to m valego to folloo yd ordres, pleascto in order yd
freand in the north to yett 15 kerseys 22 yd & 15 of 30 y of the ver best
sort to be dyed redd, & made as broad & long as possible & of a goods colleur
as formerly whah is the need full from

Ef haveing receaved the white perpetuoncos which you sended mee, finde
them much inferior to what for marly I have had boath in weight
thickness lenght, besides they were not eqaelly afforded, they soud
should hold 24 a 2 sldwieght here, & saese hold sonce 20 p batt 20½ a 21
yd in langhs as far thest, which makes them ensraordmang deare
& not to proper foo what I must have them to, all this I thought

½ yd broed & of a more sabstantall ware, broatk in weight, broats

mons in antwoort aen den ul van gisteren, heeft ul wel gedaen met over te
comen, alsoo mijne meeste goederen niet voor aenstaande donderdagh hier
sullen wesen, alhoewel heden 5 a 6 packen hebbe ontfangen maer donderdag
komender noch 10 a 12 en den sal ul aen alles connen gedient sijn, soo
bayen kerseyen als mede de lakens daer ul de staelen van heeft waer
r al sich mogh verlaeten, sal evenwel ul den precisendagh noch
schrgven op dat ul seker sijn soude a gouverno, nu naer lanck soeken
en examixeren van ul quitantien soo bevint de heer horen beke das het
capitael van het briefken van ƒ 234 siaers vercocht met den intrest
ofte verloopen van dien en aen den heer oekemans soo dat daer niets
een dayh van is te verwachten tgene van ul vrint seer qualijck gedaen is
syn capitael ende intrest te vercoopen en ul daer op noch te bewijsen
dandere van £73: 8 25 seght hij sal betaelen maer noch wel 3 maert
sal aen loopen, om de waerheyt sof te seggen ick sien daer niet veel
goet gelt voor ul van te crijgen en ul soude sich beter niet hun
verscheren blijve
